text: The Moyobamba snouted tree frog (Scinax funereus) is a frog that lives in Peru, Colombia, Ecuador, and Brazil. The adult male frog is 28.7–35.1 mm long from nose to rear end and the adult female frog is 34.2–38.6. Its skin is pale green or brown with darker brown or darker green marks. There is webbing on the back feet but not on the front feet. This frog lives in trees in primary forest and secondary forest. ==References== Category:Frogs of South America
title: Scinax funereus
